Author: GreenXOfficial
Title: ‚ñ∂Ô∏èüì£[ANN] [GreenX.Network AI ] Anouncement And Bounty Allocation] ‚úîÔ∏è
Body: Hi, I have talked to the team and we would like to clarify some points with you: 1) About the addresses on Etherscan.io: there are way more than 30 addresses that holds more tokens than showed in the token holder page. We have contacted them to update the token holders page. This page has not changed at all since the first day of our pre-sale, hence, the number is greatly different to the number of tokens that have been issued to wallets. There will always be differences between the smart-contract received funds and the token slider ‚Äì however, it should be a lot lower. So, let me show you exactly which numbers you can calculate from our smart contract Total GEX for sales (not including bonus)   Remain GEX for sales   Sold GEX   GEX price $   Total sold GEX $                                                     187,500,000.00                    180,978,848.86      6,521,151.14                    0.20               1,304,230.23  BTW, we still keep contacting with EtherScan for updating our data exactly and fully as soon. 2) Regarding the numbers of GEX shown on our website: the GEX sold included the GEX sold through private sale, public sale, commissions, and sale bonus. We have recently raised sizable private placements from family offices and HNW investors who did not pay through ETH (they are traditional investors and hence did not pay in ETH). As you may know from current market, private sale is currently stronger than public sale for many projects. Hence, we must consider the GEX tokens allocated for them to be distributed after ICO finishes because to follow ERC-20 standard, all GEX tokens are not transferable until the end of ICO. Overall, the different of the number of tokens between our smart-contract and our website is because of off-market placements, bonuses, and commissions. We don‚Äôt take into account tokens issued for bounties and airdrops.  Again, we would like to thank you for bringing this matter to us. At the end of the day, we are young people hoping to use the blockchain technology to make the world a greener place. We will work hard toward that end, which is through building our platforms and fund as many green projects as possible. We hope our answer give you clearance and continue to support our cause.
